The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, Feb. 21 (PTI): The Maharashtra government has banned the use of mobile phones in public and private schools up to Class X.          
	The ban applies to both for teachers and students. The fine for violation is Rs 50 for students and Rs 100 for teachers.                  
	 New Delhi: The information and broadcasting ministry has formed a media consultative committee to ensure regular exchange of views between the administration and various media panels in the wake of criticism over the coverage of the Mumbai terror attacks. The panel is expected to discuss concerns of media houses on regulatory, policy and procedural matters.                  
	 New Delhi: An Indian who had to return from Canada one-and-a-half months ago, leaving behind his family there, has committed suicide. Depressed because he could not meet his Canadian wife and one-year-old daughter, Vijay Sherawat, 30, hanged himself at his Dwarka home. Police said Sherawats application for Canadian citizenship had been rejected.                  
	 Lucknow: Nineteen years after 135 people were killed in the Colonelganj communal riots, a court has acquitted all 103 accused. Fourteen witnesses in the case had turned hostile.                                                                                                                           
